From 83a1ff1f100e41b4ca654bd601e28792c35902d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: FishSlayR Dev <dev@fishslayr.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 19:19:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Tournament mode step 3b: live leaderboard + host tools +
 restyled forms

- src/components/Tournament.jsx: rewritten. Lobby/TeamPicker/Leaderboard split.
  Leaderboard: RPC-ranked teams, expandable rows revealing each team's bass with
  shared thumbnails (full rival visibility, signed URLs), top-3 'counts' tags,
  Other bucket, your team highlighted, manual Refresh (Realtime is step 5), and
  your own 'not counted' markers. Host tools panel (owner-gated): close
  tournament, void/restore a catch, remove team, remove member.
- src/lib/tournament.js: leaderboard/detail/roster fetches, signed thumbnail
  URLs, getTournament meta, host-admin ops, and angler_name populated from the
  Google identity at host/join.
- src/styles/app.css: full tournament stylesheet in the app's glass/gold/eyebrow
  voice (replaces the tiny 3a toggle block). 3a forms restyled to match the
  .details label pattern. Mobile breakpoints.

Owner sees the board via ownership; members via membership (migration 06).
